name: Bulbasaur
flavor_text: There is a plant seed on its back right from the day this Pokémon is born. The seed slowly grows larger.

name: Ivysaur
flavor_text: There is a plant bulb on its back. When it absorbs nutrients, the bulb is said to blossom into a large flower.

name: Venusaur
flavor_text: A bewitching aroma wafts from its flower. The fragrance becalms those engaged in a battle.

name: Charmander
flavor_text: From the time it is born, a flame burns at the tip of its tail. Its life would end if the flame were to go out.

name: Charmeleon
flavor_text: It lashes about with its tail to knock down its foe. It then tears up the fallen opponent with sharp claws.

name: Charizard
flavor_text: Its wings can carry this Pokémon close to an altitude of 4,600 feet. It blows out fire at very high temperatures.

name: Squirtle
flavor_text: When it retracts its long neck into its shell, it squirts out water with vigorous force.

name: Wartortle
flavor_text: This Pokémon is very popular as a pet. Its fur-covered tail is a symbol of its longevity.

name: Blastoise
flavor_text: It crushes its foe under its heavy body to cause fainting. In a pinch, it will withdraw inside its shell.

name: Caterpie
flavor_text: It is covered with a green skin. When it grows, it sheds the skin, covers itself with silk, and becomes a cocoon.

name: Metapod
flavor_text: Even though it is encased in a sturdy shell, the body inside is tender. It can’t withstand a harsh attack.

name: Butterfree
flavor_text: The wings are protected by rain-repellent dust. As a result, this Pokémon can fly about even in rain.

name: Weedle
flavor_text: Often found in forests and grasslands. It has a sharp, toxic barb of around two inches on top of its head.

name: Kakuna
flavor_text: This Pokémon is in a temporary stage while making its body. It is almost completely unable to move on its own.

name: Beedrill
flavor_text: May appear in a swarm. Flies at violent speeds, all the while stabbing with the toxic stinger on its rear.

name: Pidgey
flavor_text: Does not like to fight. It hides in tall grass and so on, foraging for food such as small bugs.

name: Pidgeotto
flavor_text: The claws on its feet are well developed. It can carry prey such as an EXEGGCUTE to its nest over 60 miles away.

name: Pidgeot
flavor_text: It spreads its gorgeous wings widely to intimidate enemies. It races through the skies at Mach-2 speed.

name: Rattata
flavor_text: Its fangs are long and very sharp. They grow continuously, so it gnaws on hard things to whittle them down.

name: Raticate
flavor_text: Its rear feet have three toes each. They are webbed, enabling it to swim across rivers.

name: Spearow
flavor_text: It busily flits around here and there. Even if it is frail, it can be a tough foe that uses MIRROR MOVE.

name: Fearow
flavor_text: Its huge and magnificent wings can keep it aloft in the sky. It can remain flying a whole day without landing.

name: Ekans
flavor_text: A very common sight in grassland, etc. It flicks its tongue in and out to sense danger in its surroundings.

name: Arbok
flavor_text: The pattern on its belly appears to be a frightening face. Weak foes will flee just at the sight of the pattern.

name: Pikachu
flavor_text: It has small electric sacs on both its cheeks. If threatened, it looses electric charges from the sacs.

name: Raichu
flavor_text: Its electric charges can reach even 100,000 volts. Careless contact can cause even an Indian elephant to faint.

name: Sandshrew
flavor_text: It burrows and lives underground. If threatened, it curls itself up into a ball for protection.

name: Sandslash
flavor_text: It is adept at attacking with the spines on its back and its sharp claws while quickly scurrying about.

name: Nidoran-f
flavor_text: Though small, it must be treated with caution because of its powerfully toxic barbs. The female has smaller horns.

name: Nidorina
flavor_text: The female has a gentle temperament. It emits ultrasonic cries that have the power to befuddle foes.

name: Nidoqueen
flavor_text: The body is covered by stiff, needle- like scales. If it becomes excited, the needles bristle outwards.

name: Nidoran-m
flavor_text: Its large ears are flapped like wings when it is listening to distant sounds. It extends toxic barbs when angered.

name: Nidorino
flavor_text: It is easily angered. By swinging its well- developed horn wildly, it can even punch through diamond.

name: Nidoking
flavor_text: It is recognized by its rock-hard hide and its extended horn. Be careful with the horn as it contains venom.

name: Clefairy
flavor_text: Its adorable appearance makes it popular as a pet. However, it is rare and difficult to find.

name: Clefable
flavor_text: It has an acute sense of hearing. It can easily hear a pin being dropped nearly 1,100 yards away.

name: Vulpix
flavor_text: While young, it has six gorgeous tails. When it grows, several new tails are sprouted.

name: Ninetales
flavor_text: It has nine long tails and fur that  gleams gold. It is said to live for  1,000 years.

name: Jigglypuff
flavor_text: It captivates foes with its huge, round eyes, then lulls them to sleep by singing a soothing melody.

name: Wigglytuff
flavor_text: Its fur is extremely fine, dense, and supple. The exquisitely pleasant fur conveys an image of luxury.

name: Zubat
flavor_text: It has no eyes. Instead, it relies on its ultrasonic cries for echo location to flit about in darkness.

name: Golbat
flavor_text: It clamps down on its prey with needle- sharp fangs and drains over 10 ounces of blood in one gulp.

name: Oddish
flavor_text: Its scientific name is “Oddium Wanderus.” At night, it is said to walk nearly 1,000 feet on its two roots.

name: Gloom
flavor_text: Its pistils exude an incredibly foul odor. The horrid stench can cause fainting at a distance of 1.25 miles.

name: Vileplume
flavor_text: Its petals are the largest in the world. It fiendishly scatters allergy-causing pollen from its petals.

name: Paras
flavor_text: Growing out of the bug’s back are mushrooms called tochukaso. The mushrooms grow with the bug host.

name: Parasect
flavor_text: It scatters toxic spores from the mushroom cap. In China, the spores are used as herbal medicine.

name: Venonat
flavor_text: Its eyes act as radar, enabling it to be active in darkness. The eyes can also shoot powerful beams.

name: Venomoth
flavor_text: The wings are covered with dustlike scales. Every time it flaps its wings, it looses highly toxic dust.

name: Diglett
flavor_text: It burrows through the ground at a shallow depth. It leaves raised earth in its wake, making it easy to spot.

name: Dugtrio
flavor_text: In battle, it digs through the ground and strikes the unsuspecting foe from an unexpected direction.

name: Meowth
flavor_text: All it does is sleep during the daytime. At night, it patrols its territory with its eyes aglow.

name: Persian
flavor_text: Has a vicious temperament. Beware if it raises its tail straight up. It is a signal that it is about to pounce and bite.

name: Psyduck
flavor_text: It is constantly wracked by a headache. When the headache turns intense, it begins using mysterious powers.

name: Golduck
flavor_text: The forelegs are webbed, helping to make it an adept swimmer. It can be seen swimming elegantly in lakes, etc.

name: Mankey
flavor_text: Light and agile on its feet, and ferocious in temperament. When angered, it flies into an uncontrollable frenzy.

name: Primeape
flavor_text: It is always outrageously furious. If it gives chase, it will tenaciously track the target no matter how far.

name: Growlithe
flavor_text: Very friendly and faithful to people. It will try to repel enemies by barking and biting.

name: Arcanine
flavor_text: A Pokémon that is described in Chinese legends. It is said to race at an unbelievable speed.

name: Poliwag
flavor_text: Its slick black skin is thin and damp. A part of its internal organs can be seen through the skin as a spiral pattern.

name: Poliwhirl
flavor_text: Its two legs are well developed. Even though it can live on the ground, it prefers living in water.

name: Poliwrath
flavor_text: An adept swimmer, it knows the front crawl, butterfly, and more. It is faster than the best human swimmers.

name: Abra
flavor_text: It sleeps for 18 hours a day. It uses a variety of extrasensory powers even while asleep.

name: Kadabra
flavor_text: It happened one morning - a boy with extrasensory powers awoke in bed transformed into KADABRA.

name: Alakazam
flavor_text: It does not like physical attacks very  much. Instead, it freely uses extra­ sensory powers to defeat foes.

name: Machop
flavor_text: Its whole body is composed of muscles. Even though it’s the size of a human child, it can hurl 100 grown-ups.

name: Machoke
flavor_text: Its formidable body never gets tired. It helps people by doing work such as the moving of heavy goods.

name: Machamp
flavor_text: Its four ruggedly developed arms can launch a flurry of 1,000 punches in just two seconds.

name: Bellsprout
flavor_text: Its bud looks like a human face. Because of the bud, it is rumored to be a type of legendary mandrake plant.

name: Weepinbell
flavor_text: The leafy parts act as cutters for slashing foes. It spits a fluid that dissolves everything.

name: Victreebel
flavor_text: Lures prey into its mouth with a honeylike aroma. The helpless prey is melted with a dissolving fluid.

name: Tentacool
flavor_text: Its eyes are as transparent as crystals. From them, it shoots mysterious beams of light.

name: Tentacruel
flavor_text: It has 80 tentacles that move about freely. They can sting, causing poisoning and sharp, stabbing pain.

name: Geodude
flavor_text: Its round form makes it easy to pick up. Some people have used them to hurl at each other in a snowball fight.

name: Graveler
flavor_text: Be careful while hiking on mountain trails. GRAVELER may come rolling down the path without slowing.

name: Golem
flavor_text: It is enclosed in a hard shell that is as rugged as slabs of rock. It sheds skin once a year to grow larger.

name: Ponyta
flavor_text: Its body is light, and its legs are incredibly powerful. It can clear Ayers Rock in one leap.

name: Rapidash
flavor_text: It can gallop at a top speed of 150 miles per hour. It can race as fast as a bullet train while ablaze.

name: Slowpoke
flavor_text: It is always vacantly lost in thought, but no one knows what it is thinking about. It is good at fishing with its tail.

name: Slowbro
flavor_text: When a SLOWPOKE went hunting in the sea, its tail was bitten by a SHELLDER. That made it evolve into SLOWBRO.

name: Magnemite
flavor_text: It moves while constantly hovering. It discharges THUNDER WAVE and so on from the units at its sides.

name: Magneton
flavor_text: A linked cluster formed of several MAGNEMITE. It discharges powerful magnetic waves at high voltage.

name: Farfetchd
flavor_text: It always walks about with a plant stalk clamped in its beak. The stalk is used for building its nest.

name: Doduo
flavor_text: A two-headed Pokémon that was discovered as a sudden mutation. It runs at a pace of over 60 miles per hour.

name: Dodrio
flavor_text: An odd species that is rarely found. The three heads respectively represent joy, sadness, and anger.

name: Seel
flavor_text: Covered with light blue fur, its hide is thick and tough. It is active in bitter cold of minus 40 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: Dewgong
flavor_text: Its body is covered with a pure white fur. The colder the weather, the more active it becomes.

name: Grimer
flavor_text: Sludge exposed to X rays from the moon transformed into GRIMER. It loves feeding on filthy things.

name: Muk
flavor_text: It is usually undetectable because it blends in with the ground. Touching it can cause terrible poisoning.

name: Shellder
flavor_text: It is encased in a shell that is harder than diamond. Inside, however, it is surprisingly tender.

name: Cloyster
flavor_text: Its shell is extremely hard. It cannot be shattered, even with a bomb. The shell opens only when it is attacking.

name: Gastly
flavor_text: A being that exists as a thin gas. It can topple an Indian elephant by enveloping the prey in two seconds.

name: Haunter
flavor_text: If you get the feeling of being watched in darkness when nobody is around, HAUNTER is there.

name: Gengar
flavor_text: It is said to emerge from darkness to steal the lives of those who become lost in mountains.

name: Onix
flavor_text: It usually lives underground. It searches for food while boring its way through the ground at 50 miles per hour.

name: Drowzee
flavor_text: A descendent of the legendary animal baku, which is said to eat dreams. It is skilled at hypnotism.

name: Hypno
flavor_text: It carries a pendulum-like device. There once was an incident in which it took  away a child it hypnotized.

name: Krabby
flavor_text: It can be found near the sea. The large pincers grow back if they are torn out of their sockets.

name: Kingler
flavor_text: Its large and hard pincer has 10,000- horsepower strength. However, being so big, it is unwieldy to move.

name: Voltorb
flavor_text: A life-form whose identity is unknown. It is said to SCREECH or suddenly SELFDESTRUCT.

name: Electrode
flavor_text: It explodes in response to even minor stimuli. It is feared, with the nickname of “The Bomb Ball.”

name: Exeggcute
flavor_text: Even though it appears to be eggs of some sort, it was discovered to be a life- form more like plant seeds.

name: Exeggutor
flavor_text: It is called “The Walking Tropical Rainforest.” Each of the nuts has a face and a will of its own.

name: Cubone
flavor_text: It wears the skull of its dead mother on its head. When it becomes lonesome, it is said to cry loudly.

name: Marowak
flavor_text: It is small and was originally very weak. Its temperament turned ferocious when it began using bones.

name: Hitmonlee
flavor_text: The legs freely contract and stretch. The stretchy legs allow it to hit a distant foe with a rising kick.

name: Hitmonchan
flavor_text: The spirit of a pro boxer has infused this Pokémon. It throws punches that are faster than a bullet train.

name: Lickitung
flavor_text: Its tongue is twice the length of its body. It can be moved like an arm for grabbing food and attacking.

name: Koffing
flavor_text: Its thin, balloon-like body is inflated by horribly toxic gases. It reeks when it is nearby.

name: Weezing
flavor_text: Very rarely, a sudden mutation can result in two small KOFFING twins becoming conjoined as a WEEZING.

name: Rhyhorn
flavor_text: Strong, but not too bright, this Pokémon can shatter even a skyscraper with its charging TACKLES.

name: Rhydon
flavor_text: It begins walking on its hind legs after evolution. It can punch holes through boulders with its horn.

name: Chansey
flavor_text: It lays several eggs a day. The eggs are apparently rich in nutrients and extremely delicious.

name: Tangela
flavor_text: Blue plant vines cloak the Pokémon’s identity in a tangled mass. It entangles anything that gets close.

name: Kangaskhan
flavor_text: The female raises its offspring in a pouch on its belly. It is skilled at attacking using COMET PUNCH.

name: Horsea
flavor_text: It maintains balance using its tail, which is wound up like a coil. It may spray ink from its mouth.

name: Seadra
flavor_text: Its body bristles with sharp spikes. Carelessly trying to touch it could cause fainting from the spikes.

name: Goldeen
flavor_text: Its dorsal and pectoral fins are strongly developed like muscles. It can swim at a speed of five knots.

name: Seaking
flavor_text: The horn on its head is sharp like a drill. It bores a hole in a boulder to make its nest.

name: Staryu
flavor_text: It appears in large numbers by seashores. At night, its central core flashes with a red light.

name: Starmie
flavor_text: This Pokémon has a geometric body. Because of its body, the locals suspect that it is an alien creature.

name: Mr-mime
flavor_text: It is adept at conning people. It is said to be able to create walls out of thin air by miming.

name: Scyther
flavor_text: It tears and shreds prey with its wickedly sharp scythes. It very rarely spreads its wings to fly.

name: Jynx
flavor_text: It speaks using a language that sounds human. Research is under way to determine what is being said.

name: Electabuzz
flavor_text: It loves to feed on strong electricity. It occasionally appears around large power plants and so on.

name: Magmar
flavor_text: Found near the mouth of a volcano. This fire-breather’s body temperature is nearly 2,200 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: Pinsir
flavor_text: Its two long pincer horns are powerful. Once they grip an enemy, they won’t release until the foe is torn.

name: Tauros
flavor_text: When it is about to TACKLE, it whips its body repeatedly with its three long tails.

name: Magikarp
flavor_text: It is virtually worthless in terms of both power and speed. It is the most weak and pathetic Pokémon in the world.

name: Gyarados
flavor_text: It has an extremely aggressive nature. The HYPER BEAM it shoots from its mouth totally incinerates all targets.

name: Lapras
flavor_text: Its high intelligence enables it to understand human speech. It likes to ferry people on its back.

name: Ditto
flavor_text: It can freely recombine its own cellular structure to transform into other life- forms.

name: Eevee
flavor_text: An extremely rare Pokémon that may evolve in a number of different ways depending on stimuli.

name: Vaporeon
flavor_text: Its body’s cellular structure is similar to the molecular composition of water. It can melt invisibly in water.

name: Jolteon
flavor_text: If it is angered or startled, the fur all over its body bristles like sharp needles that pierce foes.

name: Flareon
flavor_text: It has a flame bag inside its body. After inhaling deeply, it blows out flames of nearly 3,100 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: Porygon
flavor_text: Using the most advanced technologies, scientists finally succeeded in making the first artificial Pokémon.

name: Omanyte
flavor_text: A prehistoric Pokémon that lived in the primordial sea, it swims by twisting its 10 tentacles about.

name: Omastar
flavor_text: Its tentacles are highly developed as if they are hands and feet. As soon as it ensnares prey, it bites.

name: Kabuto
flavor_text: This Pokémon was regenerated from the fossil of an ancient creature. It protects itself with a hard shell.

name: Kabutops
flavor_text: It swims freely through water. It catches prey with its scythe-like arms and drains the victim’s fluids.

name: Aerodactyl
flavor_text: It was regenerated from a dinosaur’s genetic matter that was found in amber. It flies with high-pitched cries.

name: Snorlax
flavor_text: It is not satisfied unless it eats over 880 pounds of food every day. When it is done eating, it goes promptly to sleep.

name: Articuno
flavor_text: One of the legendary bird Pokémon. With its long tail trailing behind, its flying form is magnificent.

name: Zapdos
flavor_text: One of the legendary bird Pokémon. While it is flying, it makes crackling and snapping sounds.

name: Moltres
flavor_text: One of the legendary bird Pokémon. Those seeing it are overwhelmed by its orange wings that seem to be on fire.

name: Dratini
flavor_text: Even the young can exceed 6.5 feet in length. It grows larger by repeatedly shedding skin.

name: Dragonair
flavor_text: It is said to live in seas and lakes. Even though it has no wings, it has been seen flying occasionally.

name: Dragonite
flavor_text: It can fly in spite of its big and bulky physique. It circles the globe in just 16 hours.

name: Mewtwo
flavor_text: A Pokémon whose genetic code was repeatedly recombined for research. It turned vicious as a result.

name: Mew
flavor_text: A Pokémon of South America that was thought to have been extinct. It is very intelligent and learns any move.

name: Chikorita
flavor_text: Its pleasantly aromatic leaves have the ability to check the humidity and temperature.

name: Bayleef
flavor_text: A spicy aroma emanates from around its neck. The aroma acts as a stimulant to restore health.

name: Meganium
flavor_text: MEGANIUM’s breath has the power to revive dead grass and plants. It can make them healthy again.

name: Cyndaquil
flavor_text: It usually stays hunched over. If it is angry or surprised, it shoots flames out of its back.

name: Quilava
flavor_text: This Pokémon is fully covered by nonflammable fur. It can withstand any kind of fire attack.

name: Typhlosion
flavor_text: It has a secret, devastating move. It rubs its blazing fur together to cause huge explosions.

name: Totodile
flavor_text: It is small but rough and tough. It won’t hesitate to take a bite out of anything that moves.

name: Croconaw
flavor_text: It opens its huge jaws wide when attacking. If it loses any fangs while biting, they grow back in.

name: Feraligatr
flavor_text: It is hard for it to support its own weight out of water, so it gets down on all fours. But it moves fast.

name: Sentret
flavor_text: It stands on its tail so it can see a long way. If it spots an enemy, it cries loudly to warn its kind.

name: Furret
flavor_text: There is no telling where its tail begins. Despite its short legs, it is quick at hunting RATTATA.

name: Hoothoot
flavor_text: It has a perfect sense of time. Whatever happens, it keeps rhythm by precisely tilting its head in time.

name: Noctowl
flavor_text: When it needs to think, it rotates its head 180 degrees to sharpen its intellectual power.

name: Ledyba
flavor_text: When the weather turns cold, numerous LEDYBA gather from everywhere to cluster and keep each other warm.

name: Ledian
flavor_text: The star patterns on its back grow larger or smaller depending on the number of stars in the night sky.

name: Spinarak
flavor_text: It spins a web using fine--but durable-- thread. It then waits patiently for prey to be trapped.

name: Ariados
flavor_text: A single strand of a special string is endlessly spun out of its rear. The string leads back to its nest.

name: Crobat
flavor_text: The development of wings on its legs enables it to fly fast but also makes it tough to stop and rest.

name: Chinchou
flavor_text: On the dark ocean floor, its only means of communication is its constantly flashing lights.

name: Lanturn
flavor_text: It blinds prey with an intense burst of light, then swallows the immobilized prey in a single gulp.

name: Pichu
flavor_text: Despite its small size, it can zap even adult humans. However, if it does so, it also surprises itself.

name: Cleffa
flavor_text: When numerous meteors illuminate the night sky, sightings of CLEFFA strangely increase.

name: Igglybuff
flavor_text: Its extremely flexible and elastic body makes it bounce continuously--anytime, anywhere.

name: Togepi
flavor_text: A proverb claims that happiness will come to anyone who can make a sleeping TOGEPI stand up.

name: Togetic
flavor_text: It grows dispirited if it is not with kind people. It can float in midair without moving its wings.

name: Natu
flavor_text: It usually forages for food on the ground but may, on rare occasions, hop onto branches to peck at shoots.

name: Xatu
flavor_text: In South America, it is said that its right eye sees the future and its left eye views the past.

name: Mareep
flavor_text: Its fleece grows continually. In the summer, the fleece is fully shed, but it grows back in a week.

name: Flaaffy
flavor_text: Its fluffy fleece easily stores electricity. Its rubbery hide keeps it from being electrocuted.

name: Ampharos
flavor_text: The bright light on its tail can be seen far away. It has been treasured since ancient times as a beacon.

name: Bellossom
flavor_text: Plentiful in the tropics. When it dances, its petals rub together and make a pleasant ringing sound.

name: Marill
flavor_text: The end of its tail serves as a buoy that keeps it from drowning, even in a vicious current.

name: Azumarill
flavor_text: When it plays in water, it rolls up its elongated ears to prevent their insides from getting wet.

name: Sudowoodo
flavor_text: It disguises itself as a tree to avoid attack. It hates water, so it will disappear if it starts raining.

name: Politoed
flavor_text: Whenever three or more of these get together, they sing in a loud voice that sounds like bellowing.

name: Hoppip
flavor_text: Its body is so light, it must grip the ground firmly with its feet to keep from being blown away.

name: Skiploom
flavor_text: It spreads its petals to absorb sunlight. It also floats in the air to get closer to the sun.

name: Jumpluff
flavor_text: It drifts on seasonal winds and spreads its cotton-like spores all over the world  to make more offspring.

name: Aipom
flavor_text: It lives atop tall trees. When leaping from branch to branch, it deftly uses its tail for balance.

name: Sunkern
flavor_text: It lives by drinking only dewdrops from under the leaves of plants. It is said that it eats nothing else.

name: Sunflora
flavor_text: In the daytime, it rushes about in a hectic manner, but it comes to a complete stop when the sun sets.

name: Yanma
flavor_text: Its large eyes can scan 360 degrees. It looks in all directions to seek out insects as its prey.

name: Wooper
flavor_text: When it walks around on the ground, it coats its body with a slimy, poisonous film.

name: Quagsire
flavor_text: Due to its relaxed and carefree attitude, it often bumps its head on boulders and boat hulls as it swims.

name: Espeon
flavor_text: By reading air currents, it can predict things such as the weather or its foe’s next move.

name: Umbreon
flavor_text: When darkness falls, the rings on its body begin to glow, striking fear in the hearts of anyone nearby.

name: Murkrow
flavor_text: It is said that when chased, it lures its attacker onto dark mountain trails where the foe will get lost.

name: Slowking
flavor_text: When its head was bitten, toxins entered SLOWPOKE’s head and unlocked an extraordinary power.

name: Misdreavus
flavor_text: It loves to bite and yank people’s hair from behind without warning, just to see their shocked reactions.

name: Unown
flavor_text: Its flat, thin body is always stuck on walls. Its shape appears to have some meaning.

name: Wobbuffet
flavor_text: To keep its pitch-black tail hidden, it lives quietly in the darkness. It is never first to attack.

name: Girafarig
flavor_text: Its tail, which also contains a small brain, may bite on its own if it notices an alluring smell.

name: Pineco
flavor_text: It hangs and waits for flying-insect prey to come near. It does not move about much on its own.

name: Forretress
flavor_text: It remains immovably rooted to its tree. It scatters pieces of its hard shell to drive its enemies away.

name: Dunsparce
flavor_text: If spotted, it escapes by burrowing with its tail. It can hover just slightly using its wings.

name: Gligar
flavor_text: It usually clings to cliffs. When it spots its prey, it spreads its wings and glides down to attack.

name: Steelix
flavor_text: It is said that if an ONIX lives for over 100 years, its composition changes to become diamond-like.

name: Snubbull
flavor_text: It has an active, playful nature. Many women like to frolic with it because of its affectionate ways.

name: Granbull
flavor_text: Because its fangs are too heavy, it always keeps its head tilted down. However, its BITE is powerful.

name: Qwilfish
flavor_text: The small spikes covering its body developed from scales. They inject a toxin that causes fainting.

name: Scizor
flavor_text: Its wings are not used for flying. They are flapped at high speed to adjust its body temperature.

name: Shuckle
flavor_text: It stores BERRIES inside its shell. To avoid attacks, it hides beneath rocks and remains completely still.

name: Heracross
flavor_text: Usually docile, but if disturbed while sipping honey, it chases off the intruder with its horn.

name: Sneasel
flavor_text: Vicious in nature, it drives PIDGEY from their nests and feasts on the eggs that are left behind.

name: Teddiursa
flavor_text: Before food becomes scarce in wintertime, its habit is to hoard food in many hidden locations.

name: Ursaring
flavor_text: With its ability to distinguish any smell, it unfailingly finds all food buried deep underground.

name: Slugma
flavor_text: A common sight in volcanic areas, it slowly slithers around in a constant search for warm places.

name: Magcargo
flavor_text: Its brittle shell occasionally spouts intense flames that circulate throughout its body.

name: Swinub
flavor_text: If it smells something enticing, it dashes off headlong to find the source of the aroma.

name: Piloswine
flavor_text: If it charges at an enemy, the hairs on its back stand up straight. It is very sensitive to sound.

name: Corsola
flavor_text: In a south sea nation, the people live in communities that are built on groups of these Pokémon.

name: Remoraid
flavor_text: Using its dorsal fin as a suction pad, it clings to a MANTINE’s underside to scavenge for leftovers.

name: Octillery
flavor_text: It instinctively sneaks into rocky holes. If it gets sleepy, it steals the nest of a fellow OCTILLERY.

name: Delibird
flavor_text: It nests at the edge of sharp cliffs. It spends all day carrying food to its awaiting chicks.

name: Mantine
flavor_text: Swimming freely in open seas, it may fly out of the water and over the waves if it builds up enough speed.

name: Skarmory
flavor_text: After nesting in bramble bushes, the wings of its chicks grow hard from scratches by thorns.

name: Houndour
flavor_text: To corner prey, they check each other’s location using barks that only they can understand.

name: Houndoom
flavor_text: Upon hearing its eerie howls, other Pokémon get the shivers and head straight back to their nests.

name: Kingdra
flavor_text: It sleeps deep on the ocean floor to build its energy. It is said to cause tornadoes as it wakes.

name: Phanpy
flavor_text: As a sign of affection, it bumps with its snout. However, it is so strong, it may send you flying.

name: Donphan
flavor_text: The longer and bigger its tusks, the higher its rank in its herd. The tusks take a long time to grow.

name: Porygon2
flavor_text: Further research enhanced its abilities. Sometimes, it may exhibit motions that were not programmed.

name: Stantler
flavor_text: Those who stare at its antlers will gradually lose control of their senses and be unable to stand.

name: Smeargle
flavor_text: Once it becomes an adult, it has a tendency to let its comrades plant footprints on its back.

name: Tyrogue
flavor_text: Even though it is small, it can’t be ignored because it will slug any handy target without warning.

name: Hitmontop
flavor_text: It launches kicks while spinning. If it spins at high speed, it may bore its way into the ground.

name: Smoochum
flavor_text: It always rocks its head slowly backwards and forwards as if it is trying to kiss someone.

name: Elekid
flavor_text: Even in the most vicious storm, this Pokémon plays happily if thunder rumbles in the sky.

name: Magby
flavor_text: It is found in volcanic craters. Its body heat exceeds 1,100 degrees Fahrenheit, so don’t underestimate it.

name: Miltank
flavor_text: If it has just had a baby, the milk it produces contains much more nutrition than usual.

name: Blissey
flavor_text: It has a very compassionate nature. If it sees a sick Pokémon, it will nurse the sufferer back to health.

name: Raikou
flavor_text: This Pokémon races across the land while barking a cry that sounds like crashing thunder.

name: Entei
flavor_text: A Pokémon that races across the land. It is said that one is born every time a new volcano appears.

name: Suicune
flavor_text: This Pokémon races across the land. It is said that north winds will somehow blow whenever it appears.

name: Larvitar
flavor_text: It is born deep underground. It can’t emerge until it has entirely consumed the soil around it.

name: Pupitar
flavor_text: Even sealed in its shell, it can move freely. Hard and fast, it has outstanding destructive power.

name: Tyranitar
flavor_text: Its body can’t be harmed by any sort of attack, so it is very eager to make challenges against enemies.

name: Lugia
flavor_text: It is said to be the guardian of the seas. It is rumored to have been seen on the night of a storm.

name: Ho-oh
flavor_text: A legend says that its body glows in seven colors. A rainbow is said to form behind it when it flies.

name: Celebi
flavor_text: When CELEBI disappears deep in a forest, it is said to leave behind an egg it brought from the future.

name: Treecko
flavor_text: It quickly scales even vertical walls. It senses humidity with its tail to predict the next day’s weather.

name: Grovyle
flavor_text: Its strongly developed thigh muscles give it astounding agility and jumping performance.

name: Sceptile
flavor_text: The leaves on its forelegs are as sharp as swords. It agilely leaps about the branches of trees to strike.

name: Torchic
flavor_text: It has a flame sac inside its belly that perpetually burns. It feels warm if it is hugged.

name: Combusken
flavor_text: It boosts its concentration by emitting harsh cries. Its kicks have outstanding destructive power.

name: Blaziken
flavor_text: When facing a tough foe, it looses flames from its wrists. Its powerful legs let it jump clear over buildings.

name: Mudkip
flavor_text: Its large tail fin propels it through water with powerful acceleration. It is strong in spite of its size.

name: Marshtomp
flavor_text: It is at its best when on muddy ground with poor footing. It quickly overwhelms foes struggling in mud.

name: Swampert
flavor_text: Its arms are rock-hard. With one swing, they can batter down its foe. It makes its nest on beautiful beaches.

name: Poochyena
flavor_text: It has a very tenacious nature. Its acute sense of smell lets it chase a chosen prey without ever losing track.

name: Mightyena
flavor_text: It will always obey the commands of a skilled TRAINER. Its behavior arises from its living in packs in ancient times.

name: Zigzagoon
flavor_text: A Pokémon with abundant curiosity. It shows an interest in everything, so it always zigs and zags.

name: Linoone
flavor_text: When running in a straight line, it can top 60 miles per hour. However, it has a tough time with curved roads.

name: Wurmple
flavor_text: It lives amidst tall grass and in forests. When attacked, it resists by pointing its venomous spikes at the foe.

name: Silcoon
flavor_text: It conserves its energy by moving as little as possible. It awaits evolution while drinking only a little rainwater.

name: Beautifly
flavor_text: Despite its appearance, it has an aggressive nature. It attacks by jabbing with its long, thin mouth.

name: Cascoon
flavor_text: Its body, which is made of soft silk, hardens over time. When cracks appear, evolution is near.

name: Dustox
flavor_text: It scatters horribly toxic dust when it senses danger. They tend to gather in the glow of streetlamps at night.

name: Lotad
flavor_text: It searches about for clean water. If it does not drink water for too long, the leaf on its head wilts.

name: Lombre
flavor_text: It lives at the water’s edge where it is sunny. It sleeps on a bed of water grass by day and becomes active at night.

name: Ludicolo
flavor_text: The rhythm of bright, festive music activates LUDICOLO’s cells, making it more powerful.

name: Seedot
flavor_text: If it remains still, it becomes impossible to distinguish from real nuts. It delights in surprising foraging PIDGEY.

name: Nuzleaf
flavor_text: They live in holes bored in large trees. The sound of NUZLEAF’s grass flute fills listeners with dread.

name: Shiftry
flavor_text: A Pokémon that was feared as a forest guardian. It can read the foe’s mind and take preemptive action.

name: Taillow
flavor_text: It dislikes cold seasons. They migrate to other lands in search of warmth, flying over 180 miles a day.

name: Swellow
flavor_text: If its two tail feathers are standing at attention, it is proof of good health. It soars elegantly in the sky.

name: Wingull
flavor_text: It rides upon ocean winds as if it were a glider. In the winter, it hides food around its nest.

name: Pelipper
flavor_text: It is a flying transporter that carries small Pokémon in its beak. It bobs on the waves to rest its wings.

name: Ralts
flavor_text: It is highly attuned to the emotions of people and Pokémon. It hides if it senses hostility.

name: Kirlia
flavor_text: The cheerful spirit of its TRAINER gives it energy for its psychokinetic power. It spins and dances when happy.

name: Gardevoir
flavor_text: It has the power to predict the future. Its power peaks when it is protecting its TRAINER.

name: Surskit
flavor_text: They usually live on ponds, but after an evening shower, they may appear on puddles in towns.

name: Masquerain
flavor_text: The antennae have distinctive patterns that look like eyes. When it rains, they grow heavy, making flight impossible.

name: Shroomish
flavor_text: It prefers damp places. By day it remains still in the forest shade. It releases toxic powder from its head.

name: Breloom
flavor_text: The seeds on its tail are made of toxic spores. It knocks out foes with quick, virtually invisible punches.

name: Slakoth
flavor_text: It sleeps for 20 hours every day. Making drowsy those that see it is one of its abilities.

name: Vigoroth
flavor_text: It is always hungry because it won’t stop rampaging. Even while it is eating, it can’t keep still.

name: Slaking
flavor_text: It is the world’s most slothful Pokémon. However, it can exert horrifying power by releasing pent-up energy all at once.

name: Nincada
flavor_text: Because it lived almost entirely underground, it is nearly blind. It uses its antennae instead.

name: Ninjask
flavor_text: This Pokémon is so quick, it is said to be able to avoid any attack. It loves to feed on tree sap.

name: Shedinja
flavor_text: A most peculiar Pokémon that somehow appears in a POKé BALL when a NINCADA evolves.

name: Whismur
flavor_text: It usually murmurs, but starts crying loudly if it senses danger. It stops when its ear covers are shut.

name: Loudred
flavor_text: When it stamps its feet and bellows, it generates ultrasonic waves that can blow apart a house.

name: Exploud
flavor_text: It emits a variety of sounds from the  holes all over its body. Its loud cries can be heard from over six miles away.

name: Makuhita
flavor_text: It grows stronger by enduring harsh training. It is a gutsy Pokémon that can withstand any attack.

name: Hariyama
flavor_text: It stomps on the ground to build power. It can send a 10-ton truck flying with a straight-arm punch.

name: Azurill
flavor_text: It battles by flinging around its tail, which is bigger than its body. The tail is a flotation device in water.

name: Nosepass
flavor_text: Its magnetic nose consistently faces north. Travelers check NOSEPASS to get their bearings.

name: Skitty
flavor_text: It is said to be difficult to earn its trust. However, it is extremely popular for its cute looks and behavior.

name: Delcatty
flavor_text: The favorite of trend-conscious female TRAINERS, they are used in competition for their style and fur.

name: Sableye
flavor_text: It feeds on gemstone crystals. In darkness, its eyes sparkle with the glitter of jewels.

name: Mawile
flavor_text: It uses its docile-looking face to lull foes into complacency, then bites with its huge, relentless jaws.

name: Aron
flavor_text: It eats iron to build its steel body. It is a pest that descends from mountains to eat bridges and train tracks.

name: Lairon
flavor_text: It habitually shows off its strength with the size of sparks it creates by ramming its steel body into boulders.

name: Aggron
flavor_text: It claims a large mountain as its sole territory. It mercilessly thrashes those that violate its space.

name: Meditite
flavor_text: It never skips its daily yoga training. It heightens its inner strength through meditation.

name: Medicham
flavor_text: It elegantly avoids attacks with dance- like steps, then launches a devastating blow in the same motion.

name: Electrike
flavor_text: It stores static electricity in its fur for discharging. It gives off sparks if a storm approaches.

name: Manectric
flavor_text: It rarely appears before people. It is said to nest where lightning has fallen.

name: Plusle
flavor_text: It cheers on partners while scattering sparks from its body. It climbs telephone poles to absorb electricity.

name: Minun
flavor_text: Its dislike of water makes it take shelter under the eaves of houses in rain. It uses pom-poms made of sparks for cheering.

name: Volbeat
flavor_text: It lives around clean ponds. At night, its rear lights up. It converses with others by flashing its light.

name: Illumise
flavor_text: It guides VOLBEAT to draw signs in night skies. There are scientists that study the patterns it creates.

name: Roselia
flavor_text: Its flowers give off a relaxing fragrance. The stronger its aroma, the healthier the ROSELIA is.

name: Gulpin
flavor_text: There is nothing its stomach can’t digest. While it is digesting, vile, overpowering gases are expelled.

name: Swalot
flavor_text: It can swallow a tire whole in one gulp. It secretes a horribly toxic fluid from the pores on its body.

name: Carvanha
flavor_text: It lives in massive rivers that course through jungles. It swarms prey that enter its territory.

name: Sharpedo
flavor_text: The ruffian of the seas, it has fangs that crunch through iron. It swims by jetting water from its rear.

name: Wailmer
flavor_text: When it sucks in a large volume of seawater, it becomes like a big, bouncy ball. It eats a ton of food daily.

name: Wailord
flavor_text: It is among the largest of all Pokémon. It herds prey in a pack then swallows the massed prey in one gulp.

name: Numel
flavor_text: Magma of almost 2,200 degrees Fahrenheit courses through its body. When it grows cold, the magma hardens and slows it.

name: Camerupt
flavor_text: If angered, the humps on its back erupt in a shower of molten lava. It lives in the craters of volcanoes.

name: Torkoal
flavor_text: It burns coal inside its shell. If it is attacked, it belches thick, black smoke and flees.

name: Spoink
flavor_text: It apparently dies if it stops bouncing about. It carries a pearl from CLAMPERL on its head.

name: Grumpig
flavor_text: It can gain control over foes by doing odd dance steps. The black pearls on its forehead are precious gems.

name: Spinda
flavor_text: No two SPINDA are said to have identical patterns. It confuses foes with its stumbling motions.

name: Trapinch
flavor_text: It lives in arid deserts. It makes a sloping pit trap in sand where it patiently awaits prey.

name: Vibrava
flavor_text: It generates ultrasonic waves by violently flapping its wings. After making its prey faint, it melts the prey with acid.

name: Flygon
flavor_text: It hides itself by kicking up desert sand with its wings. Red covers shield its eyes from sand.

name: Cacnea
flavor_text: It prefers harsh environments such as deserts. It can survive for 30 days on water stored in its body.

name: Cacturne
flavor_text: It lives in deserts. It becomes active at night when it hunts for prey exhausted from the desert’s heat.

name: Swablu
flavor_text: It constantly grooms its cotton-like wings. It takes a shower to clean itself if it becomes dirty.

name: Altaria
flavor_text: If you hear a beautiful melody trilling deep among mountains far from people, it is ALTARIA’s humming.

name: Zangoose
flavor_text: If it comes across a SEVIPER, its fur bristles and it assumes its battle pose. Its sharp claws are its best weapon.

name: Seviper
flavor_text: It sharpens its swordlike tail on hard rocks. It hides in tall grass and strikes unwary prey with venomous fangs.

name: Lunatone
flavor_text: Its health ebbs and flows with the lunar cycle. It brims with power when exposed to the light of the full moon.

name: Solrock
flavor_text: It absorbs solar energy during the day. Always expressionless, it can sense what its foe is thinking.

name: Barboach
flavor_text: It probes muddy riverbeds with its two long whiskers. A slimy film protects its body.

name: Whiscash
flavor_text: It makes its nest at the bottom of  swamps. It will eat anything - if it is alive, WHISCASH will eat it.

name: Corphish
flavor_text: It came from overseas. It is a very hardy creature that will quickly proliferate, even in polluted streams.

name: Crawdaunt
flavor_text: A rough customer that wildly flails its giant claws. It is said to be extremely hard to raise.

name: Baltoy
flavor_text: It was discovered in ancient ruins. While moving, it constantly spins. It stands on one foot even when asleep.

name: Claydol
flavor_text: It appears to have been born from clay dolls made by ancient people. It uses telekinesis to float and move.

name: Lileep
flavor_text: It became extinct roughly 100 million years ago. It was regenerated from a fossil using advanced techniques.

name: Cradily
flavor_text: It ensnares prey with its eight tentacles. It then melts the prey with a strong acid before feeding.

name: Anorith
flavor_text: It is a kind of Pokémon progenitor. It uses its extending claws to catch prey hiding among rocks on the seafloor.

name: Armaldo
flavor_text: Protected by a hard shell, its body is very sturdy. It skewers prey with its claws to feed.

name: Feebas
flavor_text: Ridiculed for its shabby appearance, it is ignored by researchers. It lives in ponds choked with weeds.

name: Milotic
flavor_text: MILOTIC is breathtakingly beautiful. Those that see it are said to forget their combative spirits.

name: Castform
flavor_text: It has the ability to change its form into the sun, the rain, or a snow cloud,  depending on the weather.

name: Kecleon
flavor_text: It changes body color to blend in with its surroundings. It also changes color if it is happy or sad.

name: Shuppet
flavor_text: It loves to feed on feelings like envy and malice. Its upright horn catches the emotions of people.

name: Banette
flavor_text: Strong feelings of hatred turned a puppet into a Pokémon. If it opens its mouth, its cursed energy escapes.

name: Duskull
flavor_text: Making itself invisible, it silently sneaks up to prey. It has the ability to slip through thick walls.

name: Dusclops
flavor_text: Its body is entirely hollow. When it opens its mouth, it sucks everything in as if it were a black hole.

name: Tropius
flavor_text: It lives in tropical jungles. The bunch of fruit around its neck is delicious. The fruit grows twice a year.

name: Chimecho
flavor_text: It travels by riding on winds. It cleverly uses its long tail to pluck nuts and berries, which it loves to eat.

name: Absol
flavor_text: It appears when it senses an impending natural disaster. As a result, it was mistaken as a doom-bringer.

name: Wynaut
flavor_text: It tends to move in a pack with others. They cluster in a tight group to sleep in a cave.

name: Snorunt
flavor_text: It is said that a home visited by a SNORUNT will prosper. It can withstand cold of minus 150 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: Glalie
flavor_text: It has a body of ice that won’t melt, even with fire. It can instantly freeze moisture in the atmosphere.

name: Spheal
flavor_text: Its body is covered in fluffy fur. The fur keeps it from feeling cold while it is rolling on ice.

name: Sealeo
flavor_text: It touches new things with its nose to test for smell and feel. It plays by spinning SPHEAL on its nose.

name: Walrein
flavor_text: It swims through icy seas while shattering ice floes with its large tusks. It is protected by its thick blubber.

name: Clamperl
flavor_text: It is protected by a sturdy shell. Once in a lifetime, it makes a magnificent pearl.

name: Huntail
flavor_text: It lives deep in the sea where no light ever filters down. It lights up its small fishlike tail to attract prey.

name: Gorebyss
flavor_text: Its swimming form is exquisitely elegant. With its thin mouth, it feeds on seaweed that grows between rocks.

name: Relicanth
flavor_text: It has remained unchanged for 100 million years. It was discovered during a deep-sea exploration.

name: Luvdisc
flavor_text: During the spawning season, countless LUVDISC congregate at coral reefs, turning the waters pink.

name: Bagon
flavor_text: Its steel-hard head can shatter boulders. It longingly hopes for wings to grow so it can fly.

name: Shelgon
flavor_text: Its armored body makes all attacks bounce off. The armor is too tough, however, making it heavy and somewhat sluggish.

name: Salamence
flavor_text: It becomes uncontrollable if it is enraged. It destroys everything with shredding claws and fire.

name: Beldum
flavor_text: It uses magnetic waves to converse with its kind. All the cells in its body are magnetic.

name: Metang
flavor_text: It floats midair using magnetism. Its body is so tough, even a crash with a jet plane won’t leave a scratch.

name: Metagross
flavor_text: It is formed by two METANG fusing. Its four brains are said to be superior to a supercomputer.

name: Regirock
flavor_text: It is entirely composed of rocks with no sign of a brain or heart. It is a mystery even to modern scientists.

name: Regice
flavor_text: Research revealed that its body is made of the same kind of ice that is found at the South Pole.

name: Registeel
flavor_text: It is sturdier than any kind of metal. It hardened due to pressure underground over tens of thousands of years.

name: Latias
flavor_text: It can telepathically communicate with people. It changes its appearance using its down that refracts light.

name: Latios
flavor_text: It has a docile temperament and dislikes fighting. Tucking in its forelegs, it can fly faster than a jet plane.

name: Kyogre
flavor_text: This Pokémon is said to have expanded the sea by bringing heavy rains. It has the power to control water.

name: Groudon
flavor_text: This legendary Pokémon is said to represent the land. It went to sleep after dueling KYOGRE.

name: Rayquaza
flavor_text: It has lived for hundreds of millions of years in the ozone layer. Its flying form looks like a meteor.

name: Jirachi
flavor_text: It is said to make any wish come true. It is awake for only seven days out of a thousand years.

name: Deoxys-normal
flavor_text: This DEOXYS has transformed into its aggressive guise. It can fool enemies by altering its appearance.

name: Turtwig
flavor_text: Made from soil, the shell on its back hardens when it drinks water. It lives along lakes.

name: Grotle
flavor_text: It knows where pure water wells up. It carries fellow Pokémon there on its back.

name: Torterra
flavor_text: Small Pokémon occasionally gather on its unmoving back to begin building their nests.

name: Chimchar
flavor_text: It agilely scales sheer cliffs to live atop craggy mountains. Its fire is put out when it sleeps.

name: Monferno
flavor_text: To intimidate attackers, it stretches the fire on its tail to make itself appear bigger.

name: Infernape
flavor_text: It uses a special kind of martial arts involving all its limbs. Its fire never goes out.

name: Piplup
flavor_text: Because it is very proud, it hates accepting food from people. Its thick down guards it from cold.

name: Prinplup
flavor_text: It lives alone, away from others. Apparently, every one of them believes it is the most important.

name: Empoleon
flavor_text: The three horns that extend from its beak attest to its power. The leader has the biggest horns.

name: Starly
flavor_text: They flock in great numbers. Though small, they flap their wings with great power.

name: Staravia
flavor_text: It flies around forests and fields in search of bug Pokémon. It stays within a huge flock.

name: Staraptor
flavor_text: It has a savage nature. It will courageously challenge foes that are much larger.

name: Bidoof
flavor_text: With nerves of steel, nothing can perturb it. It is more agile and active than it appears.

name: Bibarel
flavor_text: It makes its nest by damming streams with bark and mud. It is known as an industrious worker.

name: Kricketot
flavor_text: It shakes its head back to front, causing its antennae to hit each other and sound like a xylophone.

name: Kricketune
flavor_text: It crosses its knifelike arms in front of its chest when it cries. It can compose melodies ad lib.

name: Shinx
flavor_text: All of its fur dazzles if danger is sensed. It flees while the foe is momentarily blinded.

name: Luxio
flavor_text: Its claws loose electricity with enough amperage to cause fainting. They live in small groups.

name: Luxray
flavor_text: It has eyes that can see through anything. It spots and captures prey hiding behind objects.

name: Budew
flavor_text: Over the winter, it closes its bud and endures the cold. In spring, the bud opens and releases pollen.

name: Roserade
flavor_text: It attracts prey with a sweet aroma, then downs it with thorny whips hidden in its arms.

name: Cranidos
flavor_text: It lived in jungles around 100 million years ago. Its skull is as hard as iron.

name: Rampardos
flavor_text: Its powerful head butt has enough power to shatter even the most durable things upon impact.

name: Shieldon
flavor_text: A Pokémon that lived in jungles around 100 million years ago. Its facial hide is extremely hard.

name: Bastiodon
flavor_text: Any frontal attack is repulsed. It is a docile Pokémon that feeds on grass and berries.

name: Burmy
flavor_text: To shelter itself from cold, wintry winds, it covers itself with a cloak made of twigs and leaves.

name: Wormadam-plant
flavor_text: When BURMY evolved, its cloak became a part of this Pokémon’s body. The cloak is never shed.

name: Mothim
flavor_text: It loves the honey of flowers and steals honey collected by COMBEE.

name: Combee
flavor_text: A Pokémon formed by three others. It busily carries sweet floral honey to VESPIQUEN.

name: Vespiquen
flavor_text: Its abdomen is a honeycomb for grubs. It raises its grubs on honey collected by COMBEE.

name: Pachirisu
flavor_text: It makes fur balls that crackle with static electricity. It stores them with berries in tree holes.

name: Buizel
flavor_text: It has a flotation sac that is like an inflatable collar. It floats on water with its head out.

name: Floatzel
flavor_text: It floats using its well-developed flotation sac. It assists in the rescues of drowning people.

name: Cherubi
flavor_text: The small ball holds the nutrients needed for evolution. Apparently, it is very sweet and tasty.

name: Cherrim
flavor_text: It blooms during times of strong sunlight. It tries to make up for everything it endured as a bud.

name: Shellos
flavor_text: Its colors and shapes differ from region to region. In the Sinnoh region, two types are confirmed.

name: Gastrodon
flavor_text: It has a pliable body without any bones. If any part of its body is torn off, it grows right back.

name: Ambipom
flavor_text: To eat, it deftly shucks nuts with its two tails. It rarely uses its arms now.

name: Drifloon
flavor_text: A Pokémon formed by the spirits of people and Pokémon. It loves damp, humid seasons.

name: Drifblim
flavor_text: At dusk, swarms of them are carried aloft on winds. When noticed, they suddenly vanish.

name: Buneary
flavor_text: It slams foes by sharply uncoiling its rolled ears. It stings enough to make a grown-up cry in pain.

name: Lopunny
flavor_text: An extremely cautious Pokémon. It cloaks its body with its fluffy ear fur when it senses danger.

name: Mismagius
flavor_text: Its cries sound like incantations. Those hearing it are tormented by headaches and hallucinations.

name: Honchkrow
flavor_text: Becoming active at night, it is known to swarm with numerous MURKROW in tow.

name: Glameow
flavor_text: It claws if displeased and purrs when affectionate. Its fickleness is very popular among some.

name: Purugly
flavor_text: It is a brazen brute that barges its way into another Pokémon’s nest and claims it as its own.

name: Chingling
flavor_text: It emits cries by agitating an orb at the back of its throat. It moves with flouncing hops.

name: Stunky
flavor_text: It protects itself by spraying a noxious fluid from its rear. The stench lingers for 24 hours.

name: Skuntank
flavor_text: It sprays a vile-smelling fluid from the tip of its tail to attack. Its range is over 160 feet.

name: Bronzor
flavor_text: Implements shaped like it were discovered in ancient tombs. It is unknown if they are related.

name: Bronzong
flavor_text: One caused a news sensation when it was dug up at a construction site after a 2,000-year sleep.

name: Bonsly
flavor_text: It looks as if it is always crying. It is actually adjusting its body’s fluid levels by eliminating excess.

name: Mime-jr
flavor_text: It habitually mimics foes. Once mimicked, the foe cannot take its eyes off this Pokémon.

name: Happiny
flavor_text: It loves round white things. It carries an egg-shaped rock in imitation of CHANSEY.

name: Chatot
flavor_text: It can learn and speak human words. If they gather, they all learn the same saying.

name: Spiritomb
flavor_text: A Pokémon that was formed by 108 spirits. It is bound to a fissure in an odd keystone.

name: Gible
flavor_text: It nests in small, horizontal holes in cave walls. It pounces to catch prey that stray too close.

name: Gabite
flavor_text: There is a long-held belief that medicine made from its scales will heal even incurable illnesses.

name: Garchomp
flavor_text: When it folds up its body and extends its wings, it looks like a jet plane. It flies at sonic speed.

name: Munchlax
flavor_text: It wolfs down its weight in food once a day, swallowing food whole with almost no chewing.

name: Riolu
flavor_text: The aura that emanates from its body intensifies to alert others if it is afraid or sad.

name: Lucario
flavor_text: It has the ability to sense the auras of all things. It understands human speech.

name: Hippopotas
flavor_text: It lives in arid places. Instead of perspiration, it expels grainy sand from its body.

name: Hippowdon
flavor_text: It blasts internally stored sand from ports on its body to create a towering twister for attack.

name: Skorupi
flavor_text: It grips prey with its tail claws and injects poison. It tenaciously hangs on until the poison takes.

name: Drapion
flavor_text: It has the power in its clawed arms to make scrap of a car. The tips of its claws release poison.

name: Croagunk
flavor_text: Its cheeks hold poison sacs. It tries to catch foes off guard to jab them with toxic fingers.

name: Toxicroak
flavor_text: Its knuckle claws secrete a toxin so vile that even a scratch could prove fatal.

name: Carnivine
flavor_text: It attracts prey with its sweet- smelling saliva, then chomps down. It takes a whole day to eat prey.

name: Finneon
flavor_text: After long exposure to sunlight, the patterns on its tail fins shine vividly when darkness arrives.

name: Lumineon
flavor_text: It lives on the deep-sea floor. It attracts prey by flashing the patterns on its four tail fins.

name: Mantyke
flavor_text: A friendly Pokémon that captures the subtle flows of seawater using its two antennae.

name: Snover
flavor_text: It lives on snowy mountains. Having had little contact with humans, it is boldly inquisitive.

name: Abomasnow
flavor_text: It whips up blizzards in mountains that are always buried in snow. It is the abominable snowman.

name: Weavile
flavor_text: They live in cold regions, forming groups of four or five that hunt prey with impressive coordination.

name: Magnezone
flavor_text: It evolved from exposure to a special magnetic field. Three units generate magnetism.

name: Lickilicky
flavor_text: It wraps things with its extensible tongue. Getting too close to it will leave you soaked with drool.

name: Rhyperior
flavor_text: It puts rocks in holes in its palms and uses its muscles to shoot them. GEODUDE are shot at rare times.

name: Tangrowth
flavor_text: It ensnares prey by extending arms made of vines. Losing arms to predators does not trouble it.

name: Electivire
flavor_text: As its electric charge amplifies, blue sparks begin to crackle between its horns.

name: Magmortar
flavor_text: It blasts fireballs of over 3,600 degrees F from the ends of its arms. It lives in volcanic craters.

name: Togekiss
flavor_text: It will never appear where there is strife. Its sightings have become rare recently.

name: Yanmega
flavor_text: By churning its wings, it creates shock waves that inflict critical internal injuries to foes.

name: Leafeon
flavor_text: Just like a plant, it uses photosynthesis. As a result, it is always enveloped in clear air.

name: Glaceon
flavor_text: As a protective technique, it can completely freeze its fur to make its hairs stand like needles.

name: Gliscor
flavor_text: It observes prey while hanging inverted from branches. When the chance presents itself, it swoops!

name: Mamoswine
flavor_text: Its impressive tusks are made of ice. The population thinned when it turned warm after the ice age.

name: Porygon-z
flavor_text: Additional software was installed to make it a better Pokémon. It began acting oddly, however.

name: Gallade
flavor_text: A master of courtesy and swordsmanship, it fights using extending swords on its elbows.

name: Probopass
flavor_text: It freely controls three small units called Mini-Noses using magnetic force.

name: Dusknoir
flavor_text: The antenna on its head captures radio waves from the world of spirits that command it to take people there.

name: Froslass
flavor_text: It freezes foes with an icy breath nearly -60 degrees F. What seems to be its body is actually hollow.

name: Rotom
flavor_text: Its body is composed of plasma. It is known to infiltrate electronic devices and wreak havoc.

name: Uxie
flavor_text: Known as “The Being of Knowledge.” It is said that it can wipe out the memory of those who see its eyes.

name: Mesprit
flavor_text: Known as “The Being of Emotion.” It taught humans the nobility of sorrow, pain, and joy.

name: Azelf
flavor_text: Known as “The Being of Willpower.” It sleeps at the bottom of a lake to keep the world in balance.

name: Dialga
flavor_text: It has the power to control time. It appears in Sinnoh-region myths as an ancient deity.

name: Palkia
flavor_text: It has the ability to distort space. It is described as a deity in Sinnoh-region mythology.

name: Heatran
flavor_text: It dwells in volcanic caves. It digs in with its cross-shaped feet to crawl on ceilings and walls.

name: Regigigas
flavor_text: There is an enduring legend that states this Pokémon towed continents with ropes.

name: Giratina-altered
flavor_text: A Pokémon that is said to live in a world on the reverse side of ours. It appears in an ancient cemetery.

name: Cresselia
flavor_text: Shiny particles are released from its wings like a veil. It is said to represent the crescent moon.

name: Phione
flavor_text: It drifts in warm seas. It always returns to where it was born, no matter how far it may have drifted.

name: Manaphy
flavor_text: Born on a cold seafloor, it will swim great distances to return to its birthplace.

name: Darkrai
flavor_text: It can lull people to sleep and make them dream. It is active during nights of the new moon.

name: Shaymin-land
flavor_text: It lives in flower patches and avoids detection by curling up to look like a flowering plant.

name: Arceus
flavor_text: It is described in mythology as the Pokémon that shaped the universe with its 1,000 arms.

name: Victini
flavor_text: This Pokémon brings victory. It is said that Trainers with Victini always win, regardless of the type of encounter.

name: Snivy
flavor_text: It is very intelligent and calm. Being exposed to lots of sunlight makes its movements swifter.

name: Servine
flavor_text: It moves along the ground as if sliding. Its swift movements befuddle its foes, and it then attacks with a vine whip.

name: Serperior
flavor_text: It can stop its opponents’ movements with just a glare. It takes in solar energy and boosts it internally.

name: Tepig
flavor_text: It can deftly dodge its foe’s attacks while shooting fireballs from its nose. It roasts berries before it eats them.

name: Pignite
flavor_text: When its internal fire flares up, its movements grow sharper and faster. When in trouble, it emits smoke.

name: Emboar
flavor_text: It can throw a fire punch by setting its fists on fire with its fiery chin. It cares deeply about its friends.

name: Oshawott
flavor_text: It fights using the scalchop on its stomach. In response to an attack, it retaliates immediately by slashing.

name: Dewott
flavor_text: Strict training is how it learns its flowing double-scalchop technique.

name: Samurott
flavor_text: One swing of the sword incorporated in its armor can fell an opponent. A simple glare from one of them quiets everybody.

name: Patrat
flavor_text: Using food stored in cheek pouches, they can keep watch for days. They use their tails to communicate with others.

name: Watchog
flavor_text: When they see an enemy, their tails stand high, and they spit the seeds of berries stored in their cheek pouches.

name: Lillipup
flavor_text: It faces strong opponents with great courage. But, when at a disadvantage in a fight, this intelligent Pokémon flees.

name: Herdier
flavor_text: It has black, cape-like fur that is very hard and decreases the amount of damage it receives.

name: Stoutland
flavor_text: It rescues people stranded by blizzards in the mountains. Its shaggy fur shields it from the cold.

name: Purrloin
flavor_text: They steal from people for fun, but their victims can’t help but forgive them. Their deceptively cute act is perfect.

name: Liepard
flavor_text: These Pokémon vanish and appear unexpectedly. Many Trainers are drawn to their beautiful form and fur.

name: Pansage
flavor_text: This Pokémon dwells deep in the forest. Eating a leaf from its head whisks weariness away as if by magic.

name: Simisage
flavor_text: Ill tempered, it fights by swinging its barbed tail around wildly. The leaf growing on its head is very bitter.

name: Pansear
flavor_text: When it is angered, the temperature of its head tuft reaches 600° F. It uses its tuft to roast berries.

name: Simisear
flavor_text: It loves sweets because they become energy for the fire burning inside its body.

name: Panpour
flavor_text: The water stored inside the tuft on its head is full of nutrients. Plants that receive its water grow large.

name: Simipour
flavor_text: The tuft on its head holds water. When the level runs low, it replenishes the tuft by siphoning up water with its tail.

name: Munna
flavor_text: Munna always float in the air. People whose dreams are eaten by them forget what the dreams had been about.

name: Musharna
flavor_text: The mist emanating from their foreheads is packed with the dreams of people and Pokémon.

name: Pidove
flavor_text: Each follows its Trainer’s orders as best it can, but they sometimes fail to understand complicated commands.

name: Tranquill
flavor_text: It can return to its Trainer’s location regardless of the distance separating them.

name: Unfezant
flavor_text: Males swing their head plumage to threaten opponents. The females’ flying abilities surpass those of the males.

name: Blitzle
flavor_text: When thunderclouds cover the sky, it will appear. It can catch lightning with its mane and store the electricity.

name: Zebstrika
flavor_text: They have lightning-like movements. When Zebstrika run at full speed, the sound of thunder reverberates.

name: Roggenrola
flavor_text: Its ear is hexagonal in shape. Compressed underground, its body is as hard as steel.

name: Boldore
flavor_text: When it overflows with power, the orange crystal on its body glows. It looks for underground water in caves.

name: Gigalith
flavor_text: Compressing the energy from its internal core lets it fire off an attack capable of blowing away a mountain.

name: Woobat
flavor_text: Its habitat is dark forests and caves. It emits ultrasonic waves from its nose to learn about its surroundings.

name: Swoobat
flavor_text: It emits sound waves of various frequencies from its nose, including some powerful enough to destroy rocks.

name: Drilbur
flavor_text: It can dig through the ground at a speed of 30 mph. It could give a car running aboveground a good race.

name: Excadrill
flavor_text: It can help in tunnel construction. Its drill has evolved into steel strong enough to bore through iron plates.

name: Audino
flavor_text: It touches others with the feelers on its ears, using the sound of their heartbeats to tell how they are feeling.

name: Timburr
flavor_text: It fights by swinging a piece of lumber around. It is close to evolving when it can handle the lumber without difficulty.

name: Gurdurr
flavor_text: This Pokémon is so muscular and strongly built that even a group of wrestlers could not make it budge an inch.

name: Conkeldurr
flavor_text: It is thought that Conkeldurr taught humans how to make concrete more than 2,000 years ago.

name: Tympole
flavor_text: They warn others of danger by vibrating their cheeks to create a high-pitched sound.

name: Palpitoad
flavor_text: When they vibrate the bumps on their heads, they can make waves in water or earthquake-like vibrations on land.

name: Seismitoad
flavor_text: They shoot paralyzing liquid from their head bumps. They use vibration to hurt their opponents.

name: Throh
flavor_text: When it tightens its belt, it becomes stronger. Wild Throh use vines to weave their own belts.

name: Sawk
flavor_text: The sound of Sawk punching boulders and trees can be heard all the way from the mountains where they train.

name: Sewaddle
flavor_text: Leavanny dress it in clothes they made for it when it hatched. It hides its head in its hood while it is sleeping.

name: Swadloon
flavor_text: Forests where Swadloon live have superb foliage because the nutrients they make from fallen leaves nourish the plant life.

name: Leavanny
flavor_text: Upon finding a small Pokémon, it weaves clothing for it from leaves, using the cutters on its arms and sticky silk.

name: Venipede
flavor_text: Its bite injects a potent poison, enough to paralyze large bird Pokémon that try to prey on it.

name: Whirlipede
flavor_text: Protected by a hard shell, it spins its body like a wheel and crashes furiously into its enemies.

name: Scolipede
flavor_text: With quick movements, it chases down its foes, attacking relentlessly with its horns until it prevails.

name: Cottonee
flavor_text: When attacked, it escapes by shooting cotton from its body. The cotton serves as a decoy to distract the attacker.

name: Whimsicott
flavor_text: Like the wind, it can slip through any gap, no matter how small. It leaves balls of white fluff behind.

name: Petilil
flavor_text: The leaves on its head are very bitter. Eating one of these leaves is known to refresh a tired body.

name: Lilligant
flavor_text: Even veteran Trainers face a challenge in getting its beautiful flower to bloom. This Pokémon is popular with celebrities.

name: Basculin-red-striped
flavor_text: Red and blue Basculin get along so poorly, they’ll start fighting instantly. These Pokémon are very hostile.

name: Sandile
flavor_text: They live buried in the sands of the desert. The sun-warmed sands prevent their body temperature from dropping.

name: Krokorok
flavor_text: They live in groups of a few individuals. Protective membranes shield their eyes from sandstorms.

name: Krookodile
flavor_text: They never allow prey to escape. Their jaws are so powerful, they can crush the body of an automobile.

name: Darumaka
flavor_text: When its internal fire is burning, it cannot calm down and it runs around. When the fire diminishes, it falls asleep.

name: Darmanitan-standard
flavor_text: Its internal fire burns at 2,500° F, making enough power that it can destroy a dump truck with one punch.

name: Maractus
flavor_text: It uses an up-tempo song and dance to drive away the bird Pokémon that prey on its flower seeds.

name: Dwebble
flavor_text: This Pokémon can easily melt holes in hard rocks with a liquid secreted from its mouth.

name: Crustle
flavor_text: Competing for territory, Crustle fight viciously. The one whose boulder is broken is the loser of the battle.

name: Scraggy
flavor_text: Its skin has a rubbery elasticity, so it can reduce damage by defensively pulling its skin up to its neck.

name: Scrafty
flavor_text: Groups of them beat up anything that enters their territory. Each can spit acidic liquid from its mouth.

name: Sigilyph
flavor_text: They never vary the route they fly, because their memories of guarding an ancient city remain steadfast.

name: Yamask
flavor_text: Each of them carries a mask that used to be its face when it was human. Sometimes they look at it and cry.

name: Cofagrigus
flavor_text: It has been said that they swallow those who get too close and turn them into mummies. They like to eat gold nuggets.

name: Tirtouga
flavor_text: Restored from a fossil, this Pokémon can dive to depths beyond half a mile.

name: Carracosta
flavor_text: They can live both in the ocean and on land. A slap from one of them is enough to open a hole in the bottom of a tanker.

name: Archen
flavor_text: Said to be an ancestor of bird Pokémon, they were unable to fly and moved about by hopping from one branch to another.

name: Archeops
flavor_text: They are intelligent and will cooperate to catch prey. From the ground, they use a running start to take flight.

name: Trubbish
flavor_text: Inhaling the gas they belch will make you sleep for a week. They prefer unsanitary places.

name: Garbodor
flavor_text: It clenches opponents with its left arm and finishes them off with foul-smelling poison gas belched from its mouth.

name: Zorua
flavor_text: It changes into the forms of others to surprise them. Apparently, it often transforms into a silent child.

name: Zoroark
flavor_text: Bonds between these Pokémon are very strong. It protects the safety of its pack by tricking its opponents.

name: Minccino
flavor_text: They greet one another by rubbing each other with their tails, which are always kept well groomed and clean.

name: Cinccino
flavor_text: Their white fur is coated in a special oil that makes it easy for them to deflect attacks.

name: Gothita
flavor_text: Their ribbonlike feelers increase their psychic power. They are always staring at something.

name: Gothorita
flavor_text: They use hypnosis to control people and Pokémon. Tales of Gothorita leading people astray are told in every corner.

name: Gothitelle
flavor_text: Starry skies thousands of light-years away are visible in the space distorted by their intense psychic power.

name: Solosis
flavor_text: They drive away attackers by unleashing psychic power. They can use telepathy to talk with others.

name: Duosion
flavor_text: Since they have two divided brains, at times they suddenly try to take two different actions at once.

name: Reuniclus
flavor_text: When Reuniclus shake hands, a network forms between their brains, increasing their psychic power.

name: Ducklett
flavor_text: These bird Pokémon are excellent divers. They swim around in the water eating their favorite food--peat moss.

name: Swanna
flavor_text: Swanna start to dance at dusk. The one dancing in the middle is the leader of the flock.

name: Vanillite
flavor_text: The temperature of their breath is -58° F. They create snow crystals and make snow fall in the areas around them.

name: Vanillish
flavor_text: Snowy mountains are this Pokémon’s habitat. During an ancient ice age, they moved to southern areas.

name: Vanilluxe
flavor_text: Swallowing large amounts of water, they make snow clouds inside their bodies and attack their foes with violent blizzards.

name: Deerling
flavor_text: The color and scent of their fur changes to match the mountain grass. When they sense hostility, they hide in the grass.

name: Sawsbuck
flavor_text: They migrate according to the seasons. People can tell the season by looking at Sawsbuck’s horns.

name: Emolga
flavor_text: The energy made in its cheeks’ electric pouches is stored inside its membrane and released while it is gliding.

name: Karrablast
flavor_text: These mysterious Pokémon evolve when they receive electrical stimulation while they are in the same place as Shelmet.

name: Escavalier
flavor_text: They fly around at high speed, striking with their pointed spears. Even when in trouble, they face opponents bravely.

name: Foongus
flavor_text: It lures people in with its Poké Ball pattern, then releases poison spores. Why it resembles a Poké Ball is unknown.

name: Amoonguss
flavor_text: It lures prey close by dancing and waving its arm caps, which resemble Poké Balls, in a swaying motion.

name: Frillish
flavor_text: With its thin, veil-like arms wrapped around the body of its opponent, it sinks to the ocean floor.

name: Jellicent
flavor_text: The fate of the ships and crew that wander into Jellicent’s habitat: all sunken, all lost, all vanished.

name: Alomomola
flavor_text: The special membrane enveloping Alomomola has the ability to heal wounds.

name: Joltik
flavor_text: Joltik that live in cities have learned a technique for sucking electricity from the outlets in houses.

name: Galvantula
flavor_text: When attacked, they create an electric barrier by spitting out many electrically charged threads.

name: Ferroseed
flavor_text: When threatened, it attacks by shooting a barrage of spikes, which gives it a chance to escape by rolling away.

name: Ferrothorn
flavor_text: It fights by swinging around its three spiky feelers. A hit from these steel spikes can reduce a boulder to rubble.

name: Klink
flavor_text: The two minigears that mesh together are predetermined. Each will rebound from other minigears without meshing.

name: Klang
flavor_text: By changing the direction in which it rotates, it communicates its feelings to others. When angry, it rotates faster.

name: Klinklang
flavor_text: The gear with the red core is rotated at high speed for a rapid energy charge.

name: Tynamo
flavor_text: While one alone doesn’t have much power, a chain of many Tynamo can be as powerful as lightning.

name: Eelektrik
flavor_text: They coil around foes and shock them with electricity-generating organs that seem simply to be circular patterns.

name: Eelektross
flavor_text: They crawl out of the ocean using their arms. They will attack prey on shore and immediately drag it into the ocean.

name: Elgyem
flavor_text: It uses its strong psychic power to squeeze its opponent’s brain, causing unendurable headaches.

name: Beheeyem
flavor_text: It can manipulate an opponent’s memory. Apparently, it communicates by flashing its three different-colored fingers.

name: Litwick
flavor_text: Litwick shines a light that absorbs the life energy of people and Pokémon, which becomes the fuel that it burns.

name: Lampent
flavor_text: This ominous Pokémon is feared. Through cities it wanders, searching for the spirits of the fallen.

name: Chandelure
flavor_text: It absorbs a spirit, which it then burns. By waving the flames on its arms, it puts its foes into a hypnotic trance.

name: Axew
flavor_text: They use their tusks to crush the berries they eat. Repeated regrowth makes their tusks strong and sharp.

name: Fraxure
flavor_text: Since a broken tusk will not grow back, they diligently sharpen their tusks on river rocks after they’ve been fighting.

name: Haxorus
flavor_text: They are kind but can be relentless when defending territory. They challenge foes with tusks that can cut steel.

name: Cubchoo
flavor_text: When it is not feeling well, its mucus gets watery and the power of its Ice-type moves decreases.

name: Beartic
flavor_text: It can make its breath freeze at will. Very able in the water, it swims around in northern seas and catches prey.

name: Cryogonal
flavor_text: When its body temperature goes up, it turns into steam and vanishes. When its temperature lowers, it returns to ice.

name: Shelmet
